{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * In the 2nd year of the Juei era / 7th year of the Jishō era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1184]] {{ill|January 2|ja|1月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – After his failed campaign against the Taira clan, Minamoto no Yoshinaka, returning to Kyoto, launched a sudden attack on the palace and the Hōju-ji residence of Emperor Go-Shirakawa and confined the emperor. * In the 5th year of the Genbun era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1741]] {{ill|January 5|ja|1月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Tokugawa Yoshimune’s fourth son, Tokugawa Sōin, was granted a residence within the Ichibashi Gate area, thus founding the Ichibashi family. * In the 9th year of the Kansei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1798]] {{ill|January 4|ja|1月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A new calendar based on Western astronomy, known as the "Kansei Calendar," was adopted; its use began the following year. * In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 13|ja|12月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Yubisu Incident occurred.
