{ill|January 4|ja|1月4日|12=draft}}) – A new calendar based on Western astronomy, known as the "Kansei Calendar," was adopted; its use began the following year. * In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 13|ja|12月13日|12=draft}}) – The Yubisu Incident occurred.
