'''November 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|1=Butsumetsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10886789}}.

== Events ==
* In the 2nd year of the Juei era / 7th year of the Jishō era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1184|en|1184|WD=Q19728|lt=1184|1=1184}} {{ill|January 2|en|January 2|WD=Q2151|lt=January 2|1=January 2}}) – After his failed campaign against the Taira clan, Minamoto no Yoshinaka, returning to Kyoto, launched a sudden attack on the palace and the Hōju-ji residence of Emperor Go-Shirakawa and confined the emperor.
* In the 5th year of the Genbun era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1741|en|1741|WD=Q7573|lt=1741|1=1741}} {{ill|January 5|en|January 5|WD=Q2202|lt=January 5|1=January 5}}) – Tokugawa Yoshimune’s fourth son, Tokugawa Sōin, was granted a residence within the Ichibashi Gate area, thus founding the Ichibashi family.
* In the 9th year of the Kansei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1798|en|1798|WD=Q7823|lt=1798|1=1798}} {{ill|January 4|en|January 4|WD=Q2168|lt=January 4|1=January 4}}) – A new calendar based on Western astronomy, known as the "Kansei Calendar," was adopted; its use began the following year.
* In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1867|en|1867|WD=Q7715|lt=1867|1=1867}} {{ill|December 13|en|December 13|WD=Q2379|lt=December 13|1=December 13}}) – The Yubisu Incident occurred.

== Births ==

== Deaths ==
* In the 11th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1840|en|1840|WD=Q7619|lt=1840|1=1840}} {{ill|December 11|en|December 11|WD=Q2363|lt=December 11|1=December 11}}) – Emperor Kōkaku, the 119th Emperor of Japan (born 1771).
* In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1867|en|1867|WD=Q7715|lt=1867|1=1867}} {{ill|December 13|en|December 13|WD=Q2379|lt=December 13|1=December 13}}) – Itō Kōshitatarō, a palace guard (born 1867).
* Also in the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} 1867, December 13) – Tōdō Heisuke, another palace guard (born 1844).

